title: chore: check whether the keystore variables are set before using it
message:
chore: check whether the keystore variables are set before using it

After building a freshly cloned version of this repository the build
step fails because the gradle global variables for the release key store
are not set.
This commit adds a check around the signing configs to test whether
these variables are available and only if the are available sets up the
signing config.

title: chore: move "apply plugin" to bottom to get rid of warnings
message:
chore: move "apply plugin" to bottom to get rid of warnings

The gradle plugin "com.google.gms.google-services" should be included
at the bottom of the "build.gradle" file because it overwrites some
other values and will generate warnings during the build process if it
is not at the bottom of the file.

title: chore: remove flow type definitions for reactotron console
message:
chore: remove flow type definitions for reactotron console

This type definition was overwriting the host `console` type definition
which lead to many more errors.
This commit removes the file for now until we have a viable solution for
extending built-in host objects. A quick research didn't lead to any
results - maybe we'll have to duplicate the original console types into
our code too: https://github.com/facebook/flow/blob/master/lib/core.js#L858

title: chore: move custom flow type definitions into `flow-typed`
message: chore: move custom flow type definitions into `flow-typed`

title: chore: add common type definitions for libraries via flow-typed
message:
chore: add common type definitions for libraries via flow-typed

`flow-typed` is a tool and repository for library type definitions.
We can use this to install and add type definitions for some of the
third-party libraries that we use to our repository.
More information here: https://github.com/flowtype/flow-typed

title: chore: fix flow configuration to reduce errors
message:
chore: fix flow configuration to reduce errors

Including the `react-navigation/TypeDefinition.js` in the flow config
`[libs]` section led to `react-navigation` not being able to find the
type defitions itself - which created over 200 errors.
By removing the file from the `[libs]` section we can reduce the flow
errors to about 90 errors, most of them in the application code.

title: style: reformat all files via prettier command
message:
style: reformat all files via prettier command

This command is the initial execution of `npm run fmt` to format all
files via prettier.
After this command it shouldn't be necessary to run this again because
prettier will be run before every `git commit`.

title: chore: run prettier on pre-push for all staged files
message:
chore: run prettier on pre-push for all staged files

This will add a git prepush hook to run `lint-staged` with executes
prettier for all staged files (files that are added via `git add`).
See more here: https://github.com/prettier/prettier#pre-commit-hook-for-changed-files

title: chore: integrate prettier for unified code-style
message:
chore: integrate prettier for unified code-style

This adds `prettier` as a devDependency which can be executed via a
`npm run` script by running `npm run fmt`.
Prettier is a JavaScript formatter to ensure consistent code-style.
More information here: https://github.com/prettier/prettier
